---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { getBreadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/site';

const lastUpdated = 'March 15, 2025';

const jsonLd = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    name: 'Privacy Policy',
    description: "Delta Executor's privacy policy explaining how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when using our Roblox exploit software.",
    inLanguage: 'en-US',
    datePublished: '2023-01-01',
    dateModified: '2025-03-15',
    publisher: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: 'Delta Executor',
      logo: 'https://deltaaexecutor.net/assets/Delta-Executor-Icon.webp',
    },
    mainEntity: {
      '@type': 'Article',
      headline: 'Delta Executor Privacy Policy',
      author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Delta Executor Team' },
      publisher: {
        '@type': 'Organization',
        name: 'Delta Executor',
        logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://deltaaexecutor.net/assets/Delta-Executor-Icon.webp' },
      },
      datePublished: '2023-01-01',
      dateModified: '2025-03-15',
    },
  },
  getBreadcrumbSchema(Astro, [
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/privacy' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Delta Executor | Data Protection & Security"
  description="Read Delta Executor's privacy policy to understand how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    {jsonLd.map((block) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(block)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <section class="bg-bg px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-sm text-text">
        <div>
          <p>At Delta Executor, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our software and website.</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use our software or website.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">2. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">We may collect several types of information from and about users of our software and website, including:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
            <li><strong class="text-text">Personal Information:</strong> When you contact us, create an account, or participate in our community, we may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and Discord username.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Usage Data:</strong> We collect information about how you interact with our software and website, including features used, time spent, and actions taken.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Device Information:</strong> We may collect information about your device, including your IP address, operating system, browser type, and device identifiers.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Key System Data:</strong> When you use our key system, we collect information necessary to generate and validate keys, including timestamps and completion status of verification steps.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
            <li>Providing, maintaining, and improving our software and website</li>
            <li>Processing and completing transactions</li>
            <li>Sending you technical notices, updates, and support messages</li>
            <li>Responding to your comments, questions, and requests</li>
            <li>Monitoring and analyzing trends, usage, and activities</li>
            <li>Detecting, preventing, and addressing technical issues</li>
            <li>Protecting against harmful or illegal activity</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">4. Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">We may disclose your personal information in the following circumstances:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
            <li><strong class="text-text">To Service Providers:</strong> We may share your information with third-party vendors, service providers, and other contractors who perform services on our behalf.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">For Legal Purposes:</strong> We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">To Protect Rights:</strong> We may disclose your information to protect the rights, property, or safety of Delta Executor, our users, or others.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">5. Data Security</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">6. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">Our software and website may contain links to third-party websites, services, or content that are not owned or controlled by us. We have no control over, and assume no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites or services.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">7. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">Our software and website are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will delete such information from our systems.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">8. Your Choices</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">You have certain choices regarding the information you provide to us:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
            <li><strong class="text-text">Account Information:</strong> You may update, correct, or delete your account information at any time by contacting us.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Cookies:</strong> Most web browsers are set to accept cookies by default. You can usually choose to set your browser to remove or reject cookies.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Communications:</strong> You may opt out of receiving promotional communications from us by following the instructions in those communications.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">9. Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text">10. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at privacy@deltaexecut.net.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="border-t border-primary/10 pt-4 text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
